This paper deals with multiagent reinforcement learning (MARL) algorithms, which are commonly studied in the subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and multiagent systems (cs.MA). The paper also focuses on coordination among self-driving cars, which falls under the subfield of robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper deals with resource limitations and communication patterns among agents, which are relevant to the subfield of control systems (cs.SY).
